<p>$\For{a}$</p>

\[\begin{align*}
	\lim\limits_{x\to\infty} (7x^2) &amp;= 7(\infty)^2 \\
\end{align*}\]

<p>Squaring infinity would result to a larger infinity, which is still infinity.</p>

\[\begin{align*}
	\phantom{aaaaa} &amp;= 7(\infty) \\
\end{align*}\]

<p>And any number multiplied to infinity would become insignificant. Thus,</p>

\[\begin{align*}
	\lim\limits_{x\to\infty} (7x^2)  &amp;= \infty	\tagans
\end{align*}\]

<p>$\For{b}$</p>

\[\begin{align*}
	\lim\limits_{x\to-\infty} (7x^2) &amp;= 7(-\infty)^2 \\
\end{align*}\]

<p>Squaring any negative number would result to positive. Thus,</p>

\[\begin{align*}
	&amp;= 7(\infty) \\
	&amp;= \infty	\tagans
\end{align*}\]

